---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Career Coaching Programs — Kate Mas from Messy Careers"
    description="1-on-1 career coaching programs and corporate training for professionals ready to make a real move. Choose the format that fits your situation."
>
    <div class="py-12 sm:py-16">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-6">
            <div class="text-center mb-10 sm:mb-16">
                <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-primary mb-4">
                    What I Offer
                </p>
                <h1
                    class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl text-foreground mb-6"
                >
                    1-to-1 coaching
                </h1>
                <p
                    class="font-sans text-base sm:text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8"
                >
                    Private coaching tailored to where you are and where you want to go.
                    Pick the format that fits your situation.
                </p>
                <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground mb-3">Who I work with</p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    <span class="font-sans text-sm font-medium bg-secondary/50 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Do-ers moving into strategy</span>
                    <span class="font-sans text-sm font-medium bg-secondary/50 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Freelancers building their own thing</span>
                    <span class="font-sans text-sm font-medium bg-secondary/50 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Leaders at a plateau</span>
                    <span class="font-sans text-sm font-medium bg-secondary/50 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Designers stepping into leadership</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 sm:gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto items-stretch">
                <!-- Card 1 -->
                <div class="relative bg-primary p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl flex flex-col">
<p class="absolute top-5 sm:top-6 right-5 sm:right-6 font-sans text-xs font-bold text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider">3 months</p>
                    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-primary-foreground mb-4 mt-8">
                        The Pivot Program
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-sans text-primary-foreground/70 mb-4 flex-grow">
                        We go deep, build momentum, and don't let you off the hook.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-primary-foreground/10 border border-primary-foreground/20 rounded-xl p-4 mb-4">
                        <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Good fit if:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You're ready to make a real move, not just think about it
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You want accountability over time, not a one-off chat
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You're navigating a significant career pivot
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <details class="mb-4 group/details">
                        <summary class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-primary-foreground/60 uppercase tracking-wider cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center gap-1.5 hover:text-primary-foreground/90 transition-colors">
                            <svg class="w-3 h-3 transition-transform group-open/details:rotate-90" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="currentColor"><path d="M4 2l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
                            What you actually get
                        </summary>
                        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary/60 flex-shrink-0"></span>6 × 70-minute sessions
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary/60 flex-shrink-0"></span>2 × 30-minute check-ins (progress & integration)
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary/60 flex-shrink-0"></span>Email support between sessions
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary/60 flex-shrink-0"></span>Personalized take-home exercises
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </details>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                        <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-primary-foreground">€690</p>
                    </div>
                    <a href="/intro-call" class="btn-white w-full">Explore fit</a>
                    <p class="font-sans text-xs text-primary-foreground/40 text-center mt-3">Prices are in euros. VAT not applicable, art. 293B du CGI.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 2 -->
                <div class="relative bg-card p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors flex flex-col group">
                    <p class="absolute top-5 sm:top-6 right-5 sm:right-6 font-sans text-xs font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">4 weeks</p>
                    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-foreground mb-4 mt-8">
                        The Clarity Program
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground mb-4 flex-grow">
                        Cut through the noise, find what's actually blocking you, and leave with a plan.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-secondary/40 rounded-xl p-4 mb-4">
                        <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Good fit if:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You're stuck and can't figure out why
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You need clarity fast, without a long commitment
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>Staying undecided is costing you more than deciding
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <details class="mb-4 group/details">
                        <summary class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wider cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center gap-1.5 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">
                            <svg class="w-3 h-3 transition-transform group-open/details:rotate-90" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="currentColor"><path d="M4 2l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
                            What you actually get
                        </summary>
                        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>4 × 70-minute sessions
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>Email support between sessions
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>Personalized take-home exercises
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </details>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                        <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-foreground">€430</p>
                    </div>
                    <a href="/intro-call" class="btn-primary w-full">Explore fit</a>
                    <p class="font-sans text-xs text-muted-foreground/60 text-center mt-3">Prices are in euros. VAT not applicable, art. 293B du CGI.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 3 -->
                <div class="relative bg-card p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors flex flex-col group">
                    <p class="absolute top-5 sm:top-6 right-5 sm:right-6 font-sans text-xs font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">70 mins</p>
                    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-foreground mb-4 mt-8">
                        No Strings Attached
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground mb-3 flex-grow">
                        No ongoing commitment. Just get it done.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-secondary/40 rounded-xl p-4 mb-4">
                        <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Good fit if:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You have a specific challenge to solve right now
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You don't need ongoing coaching — just a sharp session
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-foreground flex items-start gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>You want an outside perspective on something concrete
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <details class="mb-4 group/details">
                        <summary class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wider cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center gap-1.5 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">
                            <svg class="w-3 h-3 transition-transform group-open/details:rotate-90" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="currentColor"><path d="M4 2l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
                            What you actually get
                        </summary>
                        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>1 × 70-minute session
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>Comprehensive written follow-up
                            </li>
                            <li class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40 flex-shrink-0"></span>One clear next step
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </details>
                    <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-foreground mb-6">€120</p>
                    <a href="/intro-call" class="btn-primary w-full">Explore fit</a>
                    <p class="font-sans text-xs text-muted-foreground/60 text-center mt-3">Prices are in euros. VAT not applicable, art. 293B du CGI.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground text-center mt-8 sm:mt-10 max-w-xl mx-auto px-2">
                If the investment feels out of reach right now, reach out anyway. I occasionally offer reduced rates for people in career transitions.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Client quote -->
    <section class="py-12 sm:py-16 bg-secondary">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-6">
            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
                <blockquote class="font-accent text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl text-foreground leading-snug mb-6">
                    "Kate's greatest talent is to <span class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">uncover your belief system</span> — and she does it at <span class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">an incredible speed</span>. That's what makes each session <span class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">so effective</span>."
                </blockquote>
                <p class="font-serif text-base text-foreground/60">Pauline</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Corporate Training Section -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24 bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-6">
            <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 sm:gap-16 items-center">
                    <div>
                        <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-secondary mb-4">
                            For organisations
                        </p>
                        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-6">
                            Corporate Training
                        </h2>
                        <p class="font-sans text-base sm:text-lg text-primary-foreground/80 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                            Career development isn't just a personal challenge — it's an organisational one too. I work with companies to build career clarity, retention, and confidence across teams through workshops, group sessions, and tailored programmes.
                        </p>
                        <a href="/intro-call" class="btn-white">Get in touch</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-3 sm:space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-primary-foreground/10 border border-primary-foreground/20 rounded-2xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-primary-foreground mb-2">Career Development Workshops</h3>
                            <p class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/70">Half-day or full-day group sessions on career clarity, transitions, and navigating uncertainty at work.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-primary-foreground/10 border border-primary-foreground/20 rounded-2xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-primary-foreground mb-2">Team Coaching Programmes</h3>
                            <p class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/70">Structured multi-week programmes for teams going through change, growth, or strategic pivots.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-primary-foreground/10 border border-primary-foreground/20 rounded-2xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-primary-foreground mb-2">Tailored to Your Needs</h3>
                            <p class="font-sans text-sm text-primary-foreground/70">Every organisation is different. Let's talk about what your team actually needs and build from there.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24 bg-background">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-6">
            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                <p class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-primary mb-4">FAQ</p>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-foreground mb-12">Questions people ask before starting</h2>
                <div class="space-y-px">
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">How does the 1-on-1 career coaching process work?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">We start with a free intro call to make sure we're a good fit — no pressure, no pitch. If we both want to move forward, we'll book your first session.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">Sessions are 70 minutes, on video — or in person if you're in Paris. We work through whatever's most alive for you — whether that's figuring out what you actually want, working through a specific decision, or unpacking what's been keeping you stuck. Between sessions you'll have email access to me, and we'll often set small experiments or actions to try before we meet again.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">I don't have a fixed framework or a formula because everyone's context is different. But I do have a way of getting to the real question fast — which is usually not the one you walked in with.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">What makes you a qualified coach?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">I hold an ICF ACC accreditation — that's the International Coaching Federation's Associate Certified Coach credential, which requires rigorous training, supervised practice hours, and ongoing development. The ICF is the global standard for professional coaching.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">Beyond the credential, I've worked with 150+ clients across tech, design, and beyond — people navigating pivots, promotions, plateaus, and everything in between. And before coaching, I spent 8+ years working in tech myself, leading teams. I know what it actually feels like to be in the messy middle.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">I'm also currently training as a Gestalt therapist and starting a BA in Psychology — because the quality of this work matters to me, and I don't think you stop learning how to do it better. I'm also regularly supervised by a mentor coach to make sure I stay objective and professional.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">How is coaching different from therapy?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">Therapy typically focuses on healing — understanding the past, processing trauma, working through mental health challenges. Coaching focuses on the future — where you want to go and what's getting in the way.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">That said, good coaching isn't shallow. We'll dig into beliefs, patterns, and fears. It just stays anchored to your professional life and what you want to do with it. If something deeper comes up that's beyond the scope of coaching, I'll say so honestly.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">How do I know if I need a career coach?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">If you're going in circles on a career question — the same doubts, the same "I don't know what I want" — and talking to friends or colleagues isn't moving you forward, a coach is probably what you're missing.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">You don't need to be in crisis. You might just feel stuck, flat, or like something needs to change but you can't name it yet. That's enough of a reason to reach out.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">If something comes up that feels bigger than career uncertainty — anxiety, depression, or something more personal — I'm trained to recognise that and will point you toward the right support.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">What if my topic isn't strictly career-related?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">It often isn't. People come in with a "career question" that turns out to be about identity, confidence, relationships with work, or what they actually value. That's all fair game.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">What I don't do is therapy. If what's coming up needs that kind of support, I'll say so. But if it's about how you show up, what you want, or what's holding you back — we can work with it.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">What are your favourite topics to work with?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">Leadership transitions, career pivots, and identity crises — the moments when you're not sure who you are professionally anymore, or who you want to become.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">I'm particularly drawn to the in-between moments: when something has ended but the next thing hasn't started yet, when a role no longer fits but you can't quite name why, when success feels hollow and you don't know what to do with that.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="group border-t border-border last:border-b">
                        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
                            <span class="font-sans font-bold text-foreground">How do you make sure I reach my goal?</span>
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-primary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 2v12M2 8h12"/></svg>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="pb-6 space-y-3">
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">Honestly? I don't — and anyone who promises that is overselling it.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">What I do is create the conditions for it. I'll challenge you, hold you accountable, and make sure you don't let yourself off the hook too easily. I'll help you get clear on what you actually want — not just what sounds good — and build a realistic path toward it.</p>
                            <p class="font-sans text-muted-foreground">The work happens in sessions, but also between them. You bring the commitment; I bring the structure, the questions, and the push.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
